summary: By the way, while playing Omega Ruby, I noticed I love so many features in that game, that I really wish they were core part of...
body:
By the way, while playing Omega Ruby, I noticed I love so many features in that game, that I really wish they were core part of the franchise by now. Namely the PokeNav (god I adored being able to see if the Pokemon wiggling in grass is a new Pokemon or something special), Contests (pls Iwantthemtoreturnnow Ilovethem), Latios/Latias soaring (I feel like I’m in minority but I loved being able to soar through the sky of Hoenn, choose where to land, explore, fight flying Pokemon specifically, the freedom of flying was so amazing to me) and well, the sneaky catch element. So adored it.

And I really like how it rewarded you for becoming the champion by giving you a Johto starter of your choice, for completing the Delta episode by giving you an Unova starter of your choice, and then defeating the League second time by giving you a Sinnoh starter of your choice. That gave me the motivation to go and actually rechallenge the league. I rarely do that, in Moon I never went a rechallenged the League, in Ultra Moon I only did it to see different final opponents (Guzma has been the hardest by far for me, god damn his Golisopod is amazing), and in X I just, quit it after I finished the Looker-related post-game. :D

ANYWAY. I hope gen 8 will give us something nice to cherish, and while I doubt it, I wish it’d bring some old feature from past games back. Like Let’s Go brought following Pokemon back. That feature has got to stay for good now.
